2014-03-08 17:08:14		[core]  /secure  passphrase <passphrase>|-delete
2014-03-08 17:08:14		                 decrypt <passphrase>|-discard
2014-03-08 17:08:14		                 set <name> <value>
2014-03-08 17:08:14		                 del <name>
2014-03-08 17:08:14		manage secured data (passwords or private data encrypted in file sec.conf)
2014-03-08 17:08:14		passphrase: change the passphrase (without passphrase, data is stored as plain text in file sec.conf)
2014-03-08 17:08:14		   -delete: delete passphrase
2014-03-08 17:08:14		   decrypt: decrypt data still encrypted (it happens only if passphrase was not given on startup)
2014-03-08 17:08:14		  -discard: discard all data still encrypted
2014-03-08 17:08:14		       set: add or change secured data
2014-03-08 17:08:14		       del: delete secured data
2014-03-08 17:08:14		Without argument, this command displays secured data in a new buffer.
2014-03-08 17:08:14		When a passphrase is used (data encrypted), it is asked by WeeChat on startup.
2014-03-08 17:08:14		It is possible to set environment variable "WEECHAT_PASSPHRASE" to prevent the prompt (this same variable is used by WeeChat on /upgrade).
2014-03-08 17:08:14		Secured data with format ${sec.data.xxx} can be used in:
2014-03-08 17:08:14		  - command line argument "--run-command"
2014-03-08 17:08:14		  - options weechat.startup.command_{before|after}_plugins
2014-03-08 17:08:14		  - proxy options: username, password
2014-03-08 17:08:14		  - irc server options: autojoin, command, password, sasl_{username|password}
2014-03-08 17:08:14		  - option relay.network.password
2014-03-08 17:08:14		  - command /eval.
2014-03-08 17:08:14		Examples:
